      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just that the silence is so loud. every time i walk through the door i expect to hear his claws on the floor or the little jingle of his collar, and then it just hits me all over again. it's like i'm just going through the motions of a life that doesn't belong to me anymore. i'm just so tired of the weight of it all. everything feels so pointless.",
